This error occurs when you specify rpm plugin and its configuration in some one pom file and try to build from parent directory. In this case, maven will run goal `rpm:rpm` on all projects, so rpm plugin will also be applied to all projects which may have no configuration for rpm plugin.

### Solution:

Move out this plugin to separate child module.

In your case, create e.g. `rpm-package` module with entire profile:

    &lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;
    &lt;project xmlns=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0&quot;
         xmlns:xsi=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance&quot;
         xsi:schemaLocation=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd&quot;&gt;
       &lt;modelVersion&gt;4.0.0&lt;/modelVersion&gt;
       &lt;parent&gt;
         &lt;groupId&gt;net.brewspberry&lt;/groupId&gt;
         &lt;!-- I would rename it, parent is not rpm anymore --&gt;
         &lt;artifactId&gt;brewspberry-rpm-parent&lt;/artifactId&gt;
         &lt;version&gt;0.1.0-SNAPSHOT&lt;/version&gt;
       &lt;/parent&gt;
       &lt;artifactId&gt;rpm-package&lt;/artifactId&gt;
       ...
       &lt;!-- move entire block &quot;profiles&quot; here --&gt;
       &lt;profiles&gt;
         &lt;profile&gt;
           &lt;id&gt;rpm-build&lt;/id&gt;
           ...
         &lt;/profile&gt;
       &lt;/profiles&gt;
     &lt;/project&gt;

And in your parent pom.xml:

    &lt;modules&gt;
      ...
      &lt;module&gt;rpm-package&lt;/module&gt;
    &lt;/modules&gt;

**Do not forget to update mapping&#39;s source paths.**

Now you can run:

    mvn clean package

Additionally, see https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9285199/how-do-i-make-this-plugin-run-only-on-non-windows-platforms if you also build on Windows.

The &quot;**group**&quot; parameter is not the usual &quot;**groupId**&quot; of the POM.
It refers instead to a **group of RPMs** which are usually defined in the file `/usr/share/doc/rpm-$version/GROUPS`.
This is mentioned in the [plugin docs][1].
You need to configure the RPM plugin with the right group; something like this:


----------

        
    
    &lt;plugins &gt;
    ...
        &lt;plugin&gt;
           &lt;groupId&gt;org.codehaus.mojo&lt;/groupId&gt;
           &lt;artifactId&gt;rpm-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
           &lt;version&gt;2.1.5&lt;/version&gt;
           &lt;configuration&gt;
               &lt;group&gt;Development/Tools&lt;/group&gt;
           &lt;/configuration&gt;
        &lt;/plugin&gt;
    ...
    &lt;/plugins&gt;


  [1]: http://www.mojohaus.org/rpm-maven-plugin/ident-params.html#group

In my case I needed to add ...

    &lt;properties&gt;
  	    &lt;project.build.sourceEncoding&gt;utf-8&lt;/project.build.sourceEncoding&gt;
	&lt;/properties&gt;

