# `tools.jar` removed from Java 9+

You&#39;re on [JDK 11][1]. No `tools.jar` found there.

[*JEP 220: Modular Run-Time Images*][2] removed both `tools.jar` and `rt.jar` from the `lib` folder, as of [Java 9][3]. 

&gt; **Removed: rt.jar and tools.jar**
&gt; 
&gt; The class and resource files previously stored in lib/rt.jar,
&gt; lib/tools.jar, lib/dt.jar, and various other internal JAR files are
&gt; now stored in a more efficient format in implementation-specific files
&gt; in the lib directory. The format of these files is not specified and
&gt; is subject to change without notice.

This change is part of adding the [*Java Platform Module System*][4], a.k.a. [*Project Jigsaw*][5].

To upgrade *Checkstyle*, use later versions, such as:

```xml
&lt;plugin&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-checkstyle-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;3.0.0&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;dependencies&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;com.puppycrawl.tools&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;checkstyle&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;8.18&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
    &lt;/dependencies&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
```

Notice the inner `dependency` block.

Consult a Maven repo for versions of [*Apache Maven Checkstyle Plugin*][6] and of [*Checkstyle*][7]. 




  [1]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_version_history#Java_11
  [2]: https://openjdk.java.net/jeps/220
  [3]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_version_history#Java_9
  [4]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_Platform_Module_System
  [5]: https://openjdk.java.net/projects/jigsaw/
  [6]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.apache.maven.plugins/maven-checkstyle-plugin
  [7]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/com.puppycrawl.tools/checkstyle

